CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Office of the Attorney General – Environmental and Natural Resources Crimes
3 Unit – Reporting Requirement
4 FOR the purpose of altering the date by which the Office of the Attorney General is required
5 to report each year to the Governor and the General Assembly on certain activities
6 of the Office’s Environmental and Natural Resources Crimes Unit and certain
7 activities taken by the Department of the Environment or the Department of Natural
8 Resources in response to findings of the Unit; and generally relating to the
9 Environmental and Natural Resources Crimes Unit.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – State Government
12 Section 6–702(a)(1)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – State Government
17 Section 6–702(d)
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0218*

2 HOUSE BILL 218
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – State Government
4 6–702.
5 (a) (1) There is an Environmental and Natural Resources Crimes Unit of the
6 Office of the Attorney General.
7 (d) On or before [November 30] OCTOBER 1 each year, the Attorney General
8 shall report to the Governor, and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of this article, the General
9 Assembly on:
10 (1) all the activities of the Unit DURING THE PREVIOUS FISCAL YEAR;
11 and
12 (2) any actions taken by the Department of the Environment or the
13 Department of Natural Resources in response to findings and recommendations of the Unit.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
15 1, 2026.
Approved:
